source: ## 2 Dimensional scenarios - dispersing over a chain of cells

This is where we disperse the population along a chain of cells, the middle of which is a 'barrier' cell, i.e., it has cc of 1/10th of the other cells. We then record the composition of the population before and after the barrier cell. 

I was convinced we had a set of consistent resutls. Alas, there was a bug in the data analysis script. The patterns look completely random.
When broken down to each gene, it doesn't look any better. This is an example (start time 31 from a range of 0-50).
## Conclusion: given the current experiment design no significant trends have been detected.
